<subSubSection pageId="197" pageNumber="801" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="197.[1375,2580,2930,3121]" pageId="197" pageNumber="801">
Because of convergent similarities between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas &amp; Wroughton" authorityYear="1907" box="[2004,2139,3008,3042]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Colomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="197" pageNumber="801" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goslingi">C. goslingi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osgood" authorityYear="1928" box="[2214,2503,3008,3042]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Nilopegamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="197" pageNumber="801" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="plumbeus">Nilopegamys plumbeus</taxonomicName>
, they were previously confused as the same species, but several diagnostic characters distinguish them. Five previously described subspecies are probably not valid. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
